<!DOCTYPE html>
<!-- Can use this page to show the output -->
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>ASD Screening Website</title>

    <%- include("./partials/csslibs.ejs") %>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/navbar.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/create-quiz.css" />
    <link rel="icon" href="/images/Group 18.png" type="image/icon type" />
  </head>

  <body>
    <%- include("partials/navbar.ejs", {page : "cvision"}) %>

    <main>
      <div class="toptext">
        <h1 style="color: #353535"></h1>
      </div>

      <header>
        <h1 style="font-size: 50px">
          Welcome to
          <span style="color: #47b3d4"
            >AI-Based Eye Contact Testing System</span
          >
          for ASD Screening
        </h1>
      </header>
      <br />
      <section style="width: 1000px; margin: 0 auto">
        <h5>
          Our computer vision-based model will take a video input of your child,
          process it, and then generate screening results based on our trained
          AI models.
        </h5>
        <br /><br />
      </section>
      <br />
      <div
        style="
          background-color: white;
          padding: 10px 10px 30px 10px;
          border-radius: 20px;
        "
      >
        <section
          style="
            margin-top: 50px;
            padding-bottom: 35px;
            border-bottom: 1px dashed #353535;
          "
        >
          <h2>Instructions for Video Capturing:</h2>
          <br />
          <ol style="font-size: 20px; text-align: left; margin-left: 400px">
            <li>
              Use a high-resolution camera to ensure clear and detailed footage.
            </li>
            <li>
              Position the camera at an appropriate angle to capture the
              individual's face, body language, and interactions with the
              environment.
            </li>
            <li>
              Ensure proper lighting to avoid shadows or glare that may obscure
              facial expressions or gestures.
            </li>
            <li>
              Natural light is preferable, but if indoors, use well-distributed
              artificial lighting.
            </li>
            <li>
              Minimize distractions and background noise to focus on the
              individual's actions and reactions.
            </li>
            <li>
              Record a sufficiently long session to capture a range of
              behaviors.
            </li>
            <li>
              Consider multiple recording sessions to observe different aspects
              of behavior over time.
            </li>
          </ol>
        </section>
        <br /><br />
        <label for="file" style="font-size: 30px; margin-top: 10px"
          >Select Resource</label
        >
        <form
          style="
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            margin-top: 15px;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 20px;
          "
          action="/fileupload"
          enctype="multipart/form-data"
          method="POST"
        >
          <div>
            <input
              style="margin-bottom: 10px; display: flex; width: 100%; gap: 10px"
              type="file"
              name="file"
              id="file"
              accept=".mp4"
            />
          </div>
          <button
            style="
              padding: 5px;
              height: 50px;
              width: 150px;
              border-radius: 20px;
              background-color: #47b3d4;
              color: white;
              outline: none;
              border: 2px solid #47b3d4;
            "
            class="btn2"
            type="submit"
          >
            Upload Resource
          </button>
        </form>
        <br />
      </div>
      <!-- Copyright -->
      <div class="cpr" style="color: #4b50b9">
        ASD Screening Website Copyright Â© 2023. All rights reserved.
      </div>
      <!-- Copyright -->
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
